                "head": [
                    {
                        "value": "Provenance"
                    }
                ],
                "p": [
                    {
                        "value": "The Felix Kusman Papers came to New York University in 2001 as part of the original acquisition of Abraham Lincoln Brigade Archives (ALBA) collections, formerly housed at Brandeis University.  The bulk of the collection was donated to ALBA by Helen Kusman in multiple installments between 1984 and 1991. Jannas Zalesky donated materials to New York University's Tamiment Library in 2010. The accession numbers associated with these gifts are 1991.018 and 2011.018."
                    }
                ]
